    "instruction": "Using metric.csv, restrict to the candidate services (checkoutservice, currencyservice, emailservice, productcatalogservice, recommendationservice). Parse timestamp with unit='s' and utc=True. Compute global p95 and p5 for each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) using the full series (do not filter first). Then filter rows to the incident window 2024-01-15 17:27:22 to 2024-01-15 17:57:22 UTC (inclusive). For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) pair produce: total_points_in_window, anomaly_count_in_window (points where value >= p95 OR value <= p5), earliest_anomaly_timestamp (UTC) if any, anomaly_direction which is 'high' if anomalies are value>=p95 or 'low' if value<=p5 (if both occur prefer the direction with more anomalies), and max_relative_violation = max((value - p95)/p95 for high anomalies, (p5 - value)/p5 for low anomalies) across anomalies (use absolute ratio). Return rows where anomaly_count_in_window>0 sorted by anomaly_count_in_window desc then by max_relative_violation desc. Limit output to top 20 pairs. Also include up to 3 example anomaly rows (timestamp, cmdb_id, kpi_name, value) per top 5 pairs."
