    "analysis": "We have identified pervasive 'socket' KPI anomalies across nearly all candidate services starting ~2024-01-15 17:30:00 UTC. Trace error_rate series were flagged but appear to be threshold artifacts (p95==0), and logs show no error_count events. To localize the root cause we need to determine which service shows the most severe socket problem (higher counts/peaks or earliest onset) and then use traces to find the most-downstream faulty service in call chains. The next atomic step is to quantify the socket anomalies per candidate service inside the incident window (counts, earliest timestamp, mean and max values) and return example rows so we can see severity and timing differences between services.",
