{
    "analysis": "We previously found pervasive 'socket' KPI anomalies across most candidate services starting ~2024-01-15 17:30:00 UTC. Trace error_rate series were flagged but appear to be threshold artifacts (global p95 == 0) and therefore unreliable. Logs show no error_count entries for candidate services during the window; currencyservice has high log.row_count but no errors. To confirm severity and pick the most likely root-cause service we need a robust, bounded metric-level check for the 'socket' KPI that follows the rules: compute global thresholds on the full series first, then filter to the incident window and quantify anomalies (counts, earliest anomaly time, mean/max values, and relative deviation from the global p95). The previous Executor attempt produced an error, so we will re-run this atomic, well-scoped analysis.",
